.bpage.fo '5) OBJECT GROUPS'-#-'SCREEN MANAGER.ttext ''.ceSection 5 -- Object Groups.te 'Section 5 -- Object Groups.ttext ''A number of objects can be declared together in a group.  When this isdone, certain actions, described in this section, may be performed onthe entire group without having to manually perform the operation on eachobject one by one.  The object ID's for the group must all be withina range, that is, all numbers between a low and high ID..center~GROUP DEFINITIONS~.te '   GROUP DEFINITIONSThese procedures allow groups to be defined and undefined..ne 32.st {.te '      GROUP.OBJECTS.ix 'GROUP.OBJECTS\GROUP.OBJECTS (gid#,lowid,highid,obj.get.bits) - Creates an object group.Returns the group ID on success, 0 otherwise..bu {\gid# - Group identifier to assign to this group.  May also beS#AutoAllocate (or S#AA).\lowid - Lowest in a range of ~object~ id's to include in the group\highid - Highest in a range of ~object~ id's to include in the group\obj.get.bits - Which events to allow (may be OR'd) - from the list in :SYNAUXS:GETLITS which includes:.bu {\get#in.char - Input character typed\get#mouse.button - Mouse press/release\get#mouse.movement - Mouse movement\get#new.timbre.info - New kbd timbre/partial\get#new.free.info - psfree/msfree/abuf change\get#new.seq.info - New seq notes/consts\get#play.scrolling - Window boundaries\get#entry.writes - A screen timbre name chg\get#prm.info - Timbre parameter change\get#dtd.info - Direct to disk info\get#poly.change - Change in poly memory\get#ertyp - Error message needed\get#ork.smpte - Get smpte change for ork\get#arrow.key - Arrow key typed\get#screen.event - Screen manager meta-event\get#program.exit - One of the program exit keys pressed.bu }.bu }.ne 8.te '      UNGROUP.OBJECTS.ix 'UNGROUP.OBJECTS\UNGROUP.OBJECTS (gid#) - Undefines an object group.  Returns 0 on successand gid# on failure..bu {\gid# - Group identifier.bu }.st }.bpage.center~GROUP OPERATIONS~.ttext ''.te '   GROUP OPERATIONSOnce a group is defined, the following procedures may be used tooperate on it..ne 29.st {.te '      SET.GROUP.GET.ix 'SET.GROUP.GET\SET.GROUP.GET (gid#,get,setting) - Enables or disables a single "get" forthe entire group.  A no-op if gid# is invalid..bu {\gid# - Group identifier\get - Which single event to turn on or off for the group.  These may NOTbe OR'd; only one may be used.  These "get.xxx" differ from the ones in GROUP.OBJECTS which are "get#xxx".  They are taken from the list in :SYNAUXS:GETLITS which includes:.bu {\get.in.char - Input character typed\get.mouse.button - Mouse press/release\get.mouse.movement - Mouse movement\get.new.timbre.info - New kbd timbre/partial\get.new.free.info - psfree/msfree/abuf change\get.new.seq.info - New seq notes/consts\get.play.scrolling - Window boundaries\get.entry.writes - A screen timbre name chg\get.prm.info - Timbre parameter change\get.dtd.info - Direct to disk info\get.poly.change - Change in poly memory\get.ertyp - Error message needed\get.ork.smpte - Get smpte change for ork\get.arrow.key - Arrow key typed\get.screen.event - Screen manager meta-event\get.program.exit - One of the program exit keys pressed.bu }\setting - Use FALSE to turn bit(s) off, TRUE to turn them on..bu }.ne 8.te '      ERASE.GROUP.OBJECTS.ix 'ERASE.GROUP.OBJECTS\ERASE.GROUP.OBJECTS (gid#) - Does an ERASE.OBJECT for all objects inthe group..bu {\gid# - Group identifier.bu }.ne 8.te '      UNDEFINE.GROUP.OBJECTS.ix 'UNDEFINE.GROUP.OBJECTS\UNDEFINE.GROUP.OBJECTS (gid#) - Does an UNDEFINE.OBJECT for all objectsin the group..bu {\gid# - Group identifier.bu }.ne 8.te '      DISABLE.GROUP.OBJECTS.ix 'DISABLE.GROUP.OBJECTS\DISABLE.GROUP.OBJECTS (gid#) - Does a DISABLE.OBJECT for all objectsin the group..bu {\gid# - Group identifier.bu }.ne 8.te '      ACTIVATE.GROUP.OBJECTS.ix 'ACTIVATE.GROUP.OBJECTS\ACTIVATE.GROUP.OBJECTS (gid#) - Does an ACTIVATE.OBJECT.RANGE for allobjects in the group..bu {\gid# - Group identifier.bu }.ne 8.te '      UPDATE.GROUP.OBJECTS.ix 'UPDATE.GROUP.OBJECTS\UPDATE.GROUP.OBJECTS (gid#) - Does an UPDATE.OBJECT for all objectsin the group..bu {\gid# - Group identifier.bu }.ne 9.te '      SET.GROUP.AUTO.ALLOCATION.ID.ix 'SET.GROUP.AUTO.ALLOCATION.ID\(!) SET.GROUP.AUTO.ALLOCATION.ID (gid#) - Same functionality asSET.AUTO.ALLOCATION.ID, but for group ID's instead..bu {\gid# - Group identifier.bu }.st }